<AbstractNarration>This statement of work (SOW) is in support of the Four-Dimensional Weather (4DWX) System, a weather-modeling and data-processing system that ATEC runs for operational support of DOD testing.  This document describes the research and development (R&amp;D), technology transfer, and operations and maintenance (O&amp;M) that the U.S. Army Test and Evaluation Command (ATEC or "government") requires from the National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR) in fiscal year (FY) 2019.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;This award reflects NSF's statutory mission and has been deemed worthy of support through evaluation using the Foundation's intellectual merit and broader impacts review criteria.</AbstractNarration>
